<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06180062 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06180062 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  ISRAEL; KIDNAPPING; VICTIM; ESCAPE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Six Israelis, kidnapped from a houseboat and told they would be killed forbeing Jewish, overpowered their Kashmiri Muslim captors, officials saidThursday. One Israeli and two abductors were killed.;    &quot;They said it was thelast second of our lives,&quot; one of the Israelis, Koby Shemesh, said on Israelarmy radio in an interview from a hospital in Srinagar. &quot;They said if we wereJews, they would have to execute us.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ISRAELIS ESCAPE CAPTORSONE KILLED FIGHTING KIDNAPPERS IN INDIA  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The Guardians of the Islamic Revolution, one of a score of Kashmiriguerrilla groups, claimed responsibility for the incident.;    Israeli victimidentified;  Two Israelis were wounded in the fighting, and one is missing,said Rajan Bakshi, deputy inspector general of Kashmir police. He identifiedthe dead Israeli as Erez Kahane.;    It was the first time a foreigner hasbeen killed in Kashmir since a separatist Muslim insurgency escalated 18months ago. Two Swedish engineers were kidnapped in March and still are beingheld by Muslim militants.;    Two women freed;  The six Israeli men and twowomen were kidnapped from the &quot;Garden of Heaven&quot; houseboat on Dal Lake onWednesday night, authorities said. The women, an Israeli and a Dutch woman,were released by their captors soon after being taken.;    The militants thentook the Israeli men to a house in downtown Srinagar, where they were boundand questioned, police quoted one of the Israelis, Haggai Caspi, as saying.;   Eventually, Caspi was able to untie himself and the others, the Indianofficial said.;    Shemesh said one of the Israelis then &quot;managed to wrestsomeone's gun, cock it and shoot while the underground (Kashmiri militant) guywas on top of him. We managed to kill another one.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Srinagar, India  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910628  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  276  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday June 28, 199100180062,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>